You are one out of hundreds of thousands. I don’t expect everyone to like my works. It’s your view and it could have been better shared. You can’t call me annoying and expect me not to take offense. That being said, I won’t dignify you with another response. Not worth my time.

So you don’t have any words for a lady irrespective of how she looks, flirting with a married man right in the presence of his wife??

I already mentioned the message I intended to pass across with the video. You have a right to interpret it however. I respect that. What I won’t have is you paint me as a brute. I said I do not mind us having a constructive discussion on the TL but you choose to throw tantrums.

I didn’t dehumanize anyone! That lady is a professional Actor who is doing excellently well for herself. She has featured in many successful projects. I wouldn’t be the first to cast Actors like her. There is Peter Dinklage( Tyrion Lannister) who is one of Hollywood’s finest.

What I wanted to achieve with the video was to present a rather irresponsible man who said he has only 15k to spare for his own children but yet could afford to give a total stranger 200k to satisfy his lustful desire. That was the the intended crux.

The Society and the people living within it create the raw materials for the Artist to create his/her Art, Although some presentation of the Art might come out as ‘sensitive’ or ‘offensive’ which is what I wish for us to discuss constructively.

Hello Mother, thank you for your comment. I see your point and honestly, I have been discussing with some of my friends as to the sensitivity of the content. I wish to object by saying; Everyone and Everything is a material for the Artist. What we may discuss is the delivery.
